The New York Yankees player with the most walks during the 1977 regular season was Reggie Jackson, with 91 walks. That same season, Reggie Jackson had 525 at-bats.

This information is based on official MLB statistics for the 1977 season. No other Yankee had more walks than Jackson that year; for example, Willie Randolph had the second-most walks on the team with 75.

